title.label: Runs great on iPad 4 mini, crashes on start up on iPad 5 mini

content.label:
I love the game. It plays well on iPad 4 mini with no problems or glitches. Looks and plays beautifully. I’ve just upgraded to a iPad 5 mini and I can’t get it to start. It constantly crashes on start up after a few seconds. It doesn’t get past the opening screen. I’ve hard started my iPad 5 mini. Deleted and reloaded the game several times and nothing works. I’ve loaded several other WarHammer and other games I had on my iPad 4 mini and they ALL play just fine except this one. 

Both are 256GB’s iPad mini’s, running the same iPadOS’s from 13 to the lates iPadOS 14.0. Both have over 100BG free space. It’s just so frustrating!

I’ve tried contacting Rodeo Games like others have and am still waiting for a response. Hopefully there’ll be a fix as I’ve read others that have this same problem with starting this game up and it crashes.

Update 9/22/20, still no update or response from RodeoGames. The last game update has been well over 4years ago. Their Twitter account hasn’t been updated for over 3years, 7months and their Facebook page hasn’t been touched since May 16, 2019, over a year ago. I don’t believe there’ll be any response or update from them at all!
